21 governments, the Fiscal Analysis Division is required to prepare a fiscal note
22 regarding the petition that includes an explanation of any such effect. The Secretary
23 of State is required to post on the Secretary of State’s Internet website any fiscal
24 note prepared by the Fiscal Analysis Division not later than 10 business days after
25 the Secretary of State receives the petition. (NRS 295.015) Existing law also
26 authorizes the description of effect of an initiative or referendum to be challenged
27 by filing a complaint in the First Judicial District Court not later than 15 days,
28 Saturdays, Sundays and holidays excluded, after a copy of the petition is placed on
29 file with the Secretary of State. (NRS 295.061) Section 2 of this bill revises the
30 deadline for posting the fiscal note prepared by the Fiscal Analysis Division on the
31 Internet website of the Secretary of State to be: (1) if the description of effect of
32 the petition is challenged in the First Judicial District, not later than 10 business
33 days after the decision of the First Judicial District Court relating to the challenge is
34 issued; or (2) if the description of effect is not challenged in the First Judicial
35 District, not later than 10 business days after the last day to file a challenge.
